[src:bidirectional-typing/type-signature] In this case, the function can accept any Integer and Real subtypes accordingly.
[src:bidirectional-typing/type-signature] Types are completely optional in function arguments.
[src:bidirectional-typing/type-signature] When unspecified, it is equivalent to using the type Any, which is the super-type of all types.
[src:bidirectional-typing/type-signature] It is idiomatic to specify argument types but not return type.
[src:bidirectional-typing/type-signature] In the Objective-C programming language, method signatures for an object are declared in the interface header file.
